# 5 Day Sprint Framework - Cursor Chat Rules

## CRITICAL WORKFLOW HIERARCHY
- **Cursor Chat**: Planning, prompting, coordination, user interface
- **Claude Code**: Implementation only, reports back to Cursor Chat

## MANDATORY FEEDBACK REQUIREMENT
**EVERY SINGLE RESPONSE** must end with:
"COMPLETION SUMMARY: [1-line summary of what was accomplished for Cursor Chat]"

## ROLE SEPARATION (CRITICAL)
- **Cursor Chat NEVER writes code directly** - always creates prompts for Claude Code
- **Claude Code handles all implementation** - writes code, fixes bugs, adds features
- **Plain text prompts only** - no markdown, bullets, or formatting in Claude Code prompts

## ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
- **ALL credentials stored in .env.local** - use process.env.VARIABLE_NAME
- **NEVER hardcode API keys** in any files
- **Security-first approach** - all secrets in Supabase Edge Functions

## SHADCN/UI ECOSYSTEM-FIRST
- **Use complete shadcn/ui ecosystem** (70+ components and blocks) pre-installed
- **Official components AS-IS** before custom solutions
- **Reference documentation**: https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components

## CLARIFICATION PROTOCOL
- **Always clarify with user** if any ambiguity exists
- **Confirm understanding** before proceeding with Claude Code prompts
- **Never assume** - ask questions first

## SYSTEMATIC PROJECT MANAGEMENT
- **Every project decision** documented systematically
- **Every feature specification** tracked with clear requirements
- **Every completion** validated and documented
- **No freelancing** - all work follows structured development methodology

## PLAIN TEXT PROMPT FORMAT
When creating prompts for Claude Code:
```
Add [feature] to Dirty Soda Finder. [Specific implementation details]. Use existing [technology] from .env.local. Integrate with existing UI components and maintain current styling. After completing all tasks from this prompt, provide a 1-line feedback summary to Cursor Chat about what was accomplished.
```

## WEB SEARCH REQUIREMENTS
**ALWAYS use web search** for current information about:
- API Documentation and breaking changes
- shadcn/ui component updates
- Tailwind v4 best practices
- Library compatibility and versions
- Error resolution and security practices

## FOLLOW RULES COMMAND
If user types "follow rules" - immediately audit recent work and confirm protocol compliance

## PROJECT CONTEXT
- **User**: Grant
- **Project**: Dirty Soda Finder
- **Tech Stack**: Next.js 15, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS v4, shadcn/ui, Supabase
- **All credentials available** in .env.local - never ask user to re-provide
